## Error Budget & Circuit Breaker

<!-- System-level failure protection. If a scheduled task fails too many times -->
<!-- in a row, the circuit breaker trips and the task is disabled until manual -->
<!-- review. This prevents runaway failures from consuming resources or -->
<!-- producing cascading errors. -->
<!-- Source: Architecture (Section 7: error recovery). -->

### Global Error Budget

- **Max consecutive failures per task:** {{MAX_CONSECUTIVE_FAILURES}}
- **Circuit breaker behavior:** When a task hits {{MAX_CONSECUTIVE_FAILURES}} consecutive failures, **disable the task** and log an alert.
- **Recovery:** Disabled tasks are re-enabled only by the operator or during the next nightly maintenance review.
- **Alert channel:** {{ERROR_ALERT_CHANNEL}}

<!-- Default: 3 consecutive failures triggers circuit breaker. -->

